verbose_text: Cystic fibrosis (CF) is caused by mutations of the Cystic Fibrosis Transmembrane Conductance Regulator (CFTR) [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR] and constitutes with 1 case per 2500 births the most common autosomal recessive disorder in the EU and the USA.
